Q. Did you find any of Wilkins's? - A. Yes; two pint pots; after our persevering, he handed over two from behind the counter, the prisoner was present at the time; he said he had just received them from the prisoner, and gave her six-pence a pound for them; Mr. Wilkins's name was upon them both;
Sarah Bethell
and Akerman both begged for mercy, and hoped we would not punish them it being the first that either of them had done,we sent for a constable to secure the parties, and I took one of the pots to Wilkins.
